<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Central Asian Foreign Ministers Arrive in Dushanbe </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403142694 Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network in Tajik 1200 
GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1403142694 </F>
<F P=104>  Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Tajik </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The foreign ministers of Uzbekistan, Kazakhstan, and 
Kyrgyzstan have arrived in Tajikistan today. A meeting of the 
foreign ministers of the five CIS states will take place at the 
Foreign Ministry of Tajikistan tomorrow. 
  Uzbek Foreign Minister Saidmukhtar Saidkasymov, Russian 
Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev, Kazakh Foreign Minister 
Tuleutay Suleymenov, Tajik Foreign Minister Rashid Olimov, and 
Kyrgyz Deputy Prime Minister Alifbek Tefshenkulov will take part 
at this meeting. 
  The main issues to be discussed at the meeting are the 
situation on the Tajik-Afghan border and the activity of the 
peacekeeping forces there. 
  Emomali Rakhmonov, the head of state and chairman of the 
Supreme Council of Tajikistan, will meet them tomorrow. Russian 
Foreign Minister Kozyrev will arrive in Dushanbe, the capital of 
our country, tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

