<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Confident of Success in Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503100494 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 
15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1503100494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russia intends to do everything possible to 
facilitate the negotiations between the leadership of Tajikistan 
and the opposition, Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev 
declared on arrival in Dushanbe from Vladivostok today. Another 
important task for Russia is to support Tajikistan as a CIS 
state, the minister said. 
  Kozyrev is meeting in Dushanbe today with the Tajik foreign 
minister and the foreign ministers of a number of other Central 
Asian states. He pointed out in particular that there must be 
no wrecking of the negotiations with the opposition as happened 
last week following the killing of Deputy Prime Minister 
Nazarshoyev. Kozyrev is convinced that, together with the Tajik 
leadership, he will succeed in settling this issue, INTERFAX 
reports. 

</TEXT>

