<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministers Hold Meetings </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503070694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0618 
GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1503070694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Galina Gridneva and Aleksandr </F>
Kharchenko] 
  [Text] Dushanbe, 15 Mar -- Russian Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev arrived in Dushanbe today to take part in the conference 
of heads of foreign policy departments of the Central Asian 
Republics and Kazakhstan and the Russian Federation. 
Consultative meetings of the foreign ministers of Russia, 
Kazakhstan, Uzbekistan, Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan also began 
this morning. 
  The consultative meetings are being held behind closed 
doors, 
but it is known that according to the preliminary agenda the 
participants in the conference are to discuss the political 
situation in Tajikistan and around it and also prospects for 
getting a dialogue under way. After the conference its 
participants will be received by Tajik Supreme Soviet Chairman 
Emomali Rakhmonov. 
  This morning it is also envisaged that Russian Foreign 
Minister Andrey Kozyrev will make a trip to one of the sectors 
of the Tajik-Afghan border. After the trip he will have a 
conversation face-to-face with head of Tajikistan Emomali 
Rakhmonov. 

</TEXT>

