<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meet With Troop Commanders </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503093294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0802 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1503093294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Aleksandr Kharchenko and Andrey </F>
Chytov] 
  [Text] Dushanbe March 15 TASS -- The foreign ministers of 
Russia, Tajikistan, Uzbekistan, Kazakhstan and Kyrgyzstan are 
conferring with the commander of the collective peacekeeping 
force in Tajikistan, Colonel-General Boris Pyankov and the 
commander of the Russian contingent of border troops in 
Tajikistan, Lieutenant-General Anatoliy Chechulin. 
  The plenary meeting, which began in the government residence 
in Dushanbe on Tuesday morning, has heard reports of General 
Pyankov and Chechulin about the situation on the Tajik-Afghan 
border, in and around the republic. 
  The plenary session was followed by talks in a narrower 
format, including between Russian Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev and Tajik Foreign Minister Rashid Olimov. 
  A Russian delegation member told ITAR-TASS the ministers 
have 
not yet decided whether or what documents should be adopted as a 
result of their meeting. 
  Generals Pyankov and Chechulin told journalists that the 
possibility of a intra-Tajik dialogue was discussed in general, 
but he did not rule out the possibility of talks between the 
Dushanbe government and the opposition in March and April. 
  Andrey Kozyrev is due to fly to the 12th border post of the 
Pyanj border group, where two attempts of penetrating Tajikistan 
from Afghanistan were reported last night. 
  Later today Kozyrev is due to meet Tajikistan's leader 
Emomali Rakhmonov for one-to-one talks. 

</TEXT>

