<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dushanbe Talks End </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503131694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1215 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1503131694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The meeting of Russian and Central Asian foreign 
ministers that was held behind closed doors ended in Dushanbe 
Tuesday at noon. A communique on the meeting and numerous 
bilateral agreements between the foreign ministries are expected 
to be signed in the afternoon. 
  Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev left Dushanbe by 
plane, probably for the 12th border post of the Pyanj unit on 
the Tajik-Afghan border. 

</TEXT>

