<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agreements Ready for Signing With Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503093694 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 0600 GMT 15 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1503093694 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] We begin with a report from Moscow by correspondent 
Ritums Rozenbergs in which he says that at the end of the first 
day of the Latvian-Russian talks, Latvian delegation chief 
Martins Virsis said that two things were not coordinated. One 
about payment for rent of the Skrunda military facility and the 
other one concerning the wording of the text of the agreement. 
However, in spite of the disagreements, there is hope that an 
agreement will be reached in the nearest future, possibly today. 
  The main achievement of yesterday's talks is an agreement 
prepared for signing on the army withdrawal and two agreements 
on social guarantees for the Russian military. It has been 
agreed in the document that pensions will be paid to Soviet army 
pensioners, that is, to those who had become pensioners by 
January `92. A new stage is characteristic of this round of 
talks, because documents which have been discussed for several 
years have practically been prepared for signing. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

