<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Supports Russian Pullout by 31 Aug </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403184894 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1700 GMT 14 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1403184894 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] As the Foreign Affairs Ministry press center 
reports, Latvian Foreign Minister Georgs Andrejevs has received 
a letter from U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher. The 
letter once again expresses U.S. Government support for the 
Russian Army withdrawal from Latvian territory by 31 August 
1994, and shows an understanding of the Latvian people's 
problems. The Skrunda issue is also mentioned and it is stated 
that the U.S. Government is considering possible financial 
support in the issue of dismantling the Skrunda [facility]. 
  Christopher also expressed understanding of the tackling of 
the citizenship issue in Latvia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

