<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   NATO Military Official Arrives for Talks in Riga </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403191094 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1700 GMT 14 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1403191094 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Field Marshal Sir Richard Vincent, chairman of the 
NATO Military Committee, arrived in Riga today. At a meeting 
with Dainis Turlais, commander of the Latvian defense forces, 
and other government representatives, Vincent discussed Latvia's 
participation in the NATO Partnership for Peace program and the 
course of the establishment of a Baltic peacekeeping battalion. 
The Latvian representatives familiarized the guest with the 
structure of the Latvian defense forces and problems of 
legislation related to the defense forces. This is the first 
visit to Latvia by such a high-ranking NATO official. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-16224 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov050_u_94006" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-050 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
