<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further Details </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1403210694 Tallinn BNS in English 1617 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1403210694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Daugavpils, Latvia, Mar 14, BNS -- The Russian army 
Command and the Latvian Daugavpils region administration signed 
the handover-takeover papers of a former Soviet military 
airfield at Lociki. 
  The parties agreed on all paragraphs of the document except 
on the material value of the airfield compound. They decided to 
view the issue separately. 
  The Russian military persons assess the total value of all 
installations at 9 billion Russian rubles, or around 5.2 million 
U.S. dollars. Latvia, however, prices the compound at 4 billion 
Russian rubles, or 2.3 million dollars. 
  The sums have to be coordinated by the Northwest Army Group 
command and the Latvian Finance Ministry. 
  The local authorities claim that the Lociki airfield was the 
last Russian military installation in the Daugavpils region. 

</TEXT>

