<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agreement Avoiding Dual Taxation Signed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403225494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 2027 
GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1403225494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Taras Lariokhin] </F>
  [Text] The Hague, 14 Mar -- The integration of the 
Russian-speaking population into a society with a diverse 
culture is the main condition for stable internal development in 
Latvia and for the establishment of the necessary neighborly 
relations with Russia, Ruud Lubbers, the prime minister of the 
Netherlands, said at a dinner in honor of his colleague Valdis 
Birkavs. The prime minister of the Latvian Republic arrived in 
Holland today on a three-day visit. 
  In his turn, V. Birkavs stressed that Latvia is going 
through 
a difficult, transitional period in its development now. It is 
made even more complicated by difficulties in its relations with 
Russia. Nevertheless, the head of the Latvian Government said, 
the people of the Latvian Republic believe in the prospects for 
democratic development in the country and hope for the support 
of other nations. Latvia has firmly declared its intent to 
gradually become a member of the European Union and to join 
international security structures. In this connection, the 
prime minister of Latvia asked the Netherlands for support. 
  Today, the sides signed two agreements -- on avoiding dual 
taxation and on protecting investments. V. Birkavs expressed 
the hope that even more important bilateral economic agreements 
would be drawn up soon. 

</TEXT>

