<H3> <TI>   False Bomb Alert Disrupts Landsbergis Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1403210294 Tallinn BNS in English 1820 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1403210294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, Mar 14, BNS -- A false warning about a 
bomb placed inside the culture center of the Lithuanian town of 
Ignalina interrupted a public meeting with Vytautas Landsbergis, 
leader of the Lithuanian parliament's rightist opposition. 
  The opposition's spokeswoman confirmed that a policemen came 
into the auditorium of the center at the very beginning of the 
meeting and announced that an unidentified person threatened 
with a bomb explosion. 
  The police searched the entire building but found no 
explosives. No more incidents occurred during the remaining part 
of the gathering. 

</TEXT>

