<H3> <TI>   Visit Said Unaffected by Yeltsin's Absence </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503142594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1319 
GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1503142594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Boris Krivoshey and </F>
Dmitriy Chubarov] 
  [Text] Moscow, 15 Mar -- Tsutomu Hata, the Japanese foreign 
minister, is to pay an official visit to Russia in the next few 
days, Grigoriy Karasin, the head of the department of press and 
information of the Russian Foreign Ministry, told Itar-Tass 
today. 
  In the words of the Russian diplomat, "the holiday of 
Russian 
President Boris Yeltsin, who is in Sochi, will in no way affect 
the political content and the level of the official visit by the 
Japanese foreign minister." 
  The program of the visit, Grigoriy Karasin added, shows that 
Russia attaches great significance to its relations with Japan. 
During his stay in Russia, the Japanese minister is expected to 
meet Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin and Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev. 

