<H3> <TI>   Russia No Longer Seeking `Immediate' Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403181594 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy in Russian 
1605 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1403181594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russia and the United States continue to be partners 
in spite of all the trials and tribulations that bilateral 
relations have been subjected to of late. This was stated in 
Vladivostok today by Foreign Minister Kozyrev after his talks 
with U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher. The problem of 
a settlement in Bosnia-Herzegovina and the situation in the Near 
East were also discussed during the meeting. 
  Russia is no longer insisting on the immediate holding of a 
second international conference on the Near East, Andrey Kozyrev 
disclosed. He said that the most important thing now was to 
complete work on the implementation of the agreement on Gaza and 
Jericho. 

</TEXT>

