<H3> <TI>   No Agreement Reached With Latvia on Skrunda Radar Station </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403215294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2024 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1403215294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Bazhenov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow March 14 TASS -- Russia and Latvia have 
failed to come to an agreement on Russia's payment for using a 
radar station in Skrunda (Latvia). 
  A regular round of Russo-Latvian talks began here on Monday. 
  The two delegations reached an agreement on social welfare 
guarantees for the retired Russian military. According to the 
agreement, those of them who permanently resided in Latvia as of 
January 28, 1992, are "guaranteed the right to unhindered 
residence in Lithuania and use of their movable property and 
real estate". 
  The agenda for the current round of talks includes 
discussions of an agreement on Russian troop withdrawal from 
Latvia and an agreement on legal status, conditions, terms and 
order of work of the Russian radar station in Skrunda. 

</TEXT>

