Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The latest round of Russian-Latvian talks on 
military issues began in Moscow today. Both sides are placing 
great hopes on this round. Sergey Prikhodko, a Russian Foreign 
Ministry spokesman, was interviewed by our correspondent: 
  [Begin Prikhodko recording] We are very hopeful. It appears 
to us that contacts between experts from the two delegations on 
the eve of the talks have helped to achieve further progress 
toward agreement on outstanding questions. We hope that 
agreement on the technical questions that experts have not yet 
