<H3> <TI>   Polish Prime Minister Pawlak Holds Talks in Moscow </TI></H3>
<H4>   Urges Raw Materials, Transport Accords </H4>
<F P=102> LD1503094594 Warsaw PAP in English 0811 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1503094594 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, March 15 -- Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak 
said starting his visit to Moscow on Monday that it was high 
time that Poland and Russia gave up mutual declarations and 
stopped talking about assistance but proceeded to concrete steps 
beneficial to both countries. 
  Pawlak said he would like to translate the language of 
treaties and accords into practical actions. He said he meant 
primarily long-term agreements on strategic raw materials and 
steps to build a gas pipeline from Russia to Western Europe, a 
railway line and a highway linking Berlin, Warsaw and Moscow. 

</TEXT>

