Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Ivan Ivanov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow March 15 TASS -- Russian and Polish prime 
ministers met in the Russian Government house today to consider 
closer interaction in the economic field. They are working 
towards the signing of an intergovernmental agreement on the 
principles of Russian citizens' labour activity on Polish 
territory and Polish citizens on Russian territory, as well as 
an inter-governmental agreement on cooperation in the 
anti-monopoly activity. 
  The two premiers first met for a one-to-one talk and are due 
to continue negotiations in a broader format within the frame of 
the Polish Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak's official visit to 
the Russian capital. 

