<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   British Agent High-Ranking Member of Arms Industry </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403160094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1406 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1403160094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A well-informed source in Russia's Federal 
Counterintelligence Service confirmed that the British agent 
detained in Moscow last January was Russian citizen Vadim 
Sintsov, who held a high post in the arms industry concern SMM. 
  According to the Federal Counterintelligence Service, he 
passed over information about Russia's defense potential and 
test defense projects to British intelligence agencies. 
  The source did not confirm, however, that Sintsov had worked 
with the British intelligence agencies since 1986. He said that 
he had been recruited much later, but refused to give the exact 
time or assess the damage inflicted on Russia. 

</TEXT>

