<H3> <TI>   Abkhazia Reports Georgian Troops Still Amassing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403162294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1359 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1403162294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Irina Shchegoleva] </F>
  [Text] Sochi March 14 TASS -- Georgian troops continue to 
mass along the Inguri River separating Georgia from Abkhazia, 
according to the Abkhazian Defence Ministry. 
  The ministry said subversive groups are infiltrating the 
Galiy District. To combat crime and prevent possible acts of 
sabotage, the Abkhazian Government has ruled to establish 
special OMON [Special Purpose Militia Detachment] troops, 
Abkhazian Ministry of the Press and Information officials told 
ITAR-TASS on Monday. 
  Tuesday, March 15, will mark a year since the failure of the 
Abkhazian offensive on Sukhumi, capital of the 
independence-seeking republic, which resulted in mass casualties 
and heavy damage. Tomorrow residents of Abkhazia will mourn the 
victims of the war. 

</TEXT>

