<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Talks With Abkhazia Interrupted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503155094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1404 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1503155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The talks on settling the Georgian-Abkhazian 
conflict will not be continued until the Georgian parliament 
cancels its decision of dissolving the Abkhazian parliament, 
Chairman of the Abkhazian parliament Vladislav Ardzinba told 
Interfax after a press conference in Moscow on Tuesday. 
  He also said that the peace process was over and laid the 
entire blame for this on Georgia. 
  On March 10, the Georgian parliament charged Abkhazia's 
Council of Ministers with the task of performing the Abkhazian 
parliament's functions pending early parliamentary elections, 
and granted the Council of Ministers the status of a temporarily 
discharged body. 
  The Georgian parliament's resolution says that all legal 
acts 
passed by the Abkhazian separatists shall be considered invalid. 

</TEXT>

