<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Abkhazia Reportedly Unopposed to UN Presence </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1503135794 Yerevan SNARK in English 1007 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1503135794 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, March 15 (SNARK)--"Shevardnadze's visit to 
UN was an attempt to win back by diplomatic means what had been 
lost in Abkhazian war. By means of the UN peacemaking forces, 
and under the thesis of Georgia's territorial integrity, 
Shevardnadze attempts to provide this integrity de-facto". This 
was the comment given to SNARK correspondent in Moscow by Zurab 
Achba, the Chairman of Legislation Committee in Abkhazian 
Parliament, while he spoke on the Georgian head visit to the USA. 
  As Achba told, the Abkhazian leadership does not mind the 
presence of the UN peacekeeping forces in the conflict zone. 
"We only object those functions which they are intended to be 
given. Peace forces are entitled to prevent the military 
actions, and should be dislocated along the confrontation line, 
not on the entire territory of Abkhazia", declared Achba. 

</TEXT>

