<H3> <TI>   Officials Discuss Missing Persons </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403190994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1745 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1403190994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Irina Shchegoleva] </F>
  [Text] Sochi March 14 TASS -- Georgian and Abkhazian 
representatives met at a border-guard post at the Psou River on 
Monday to discuss exchange of prisoners of war and search for 
missing persons. 
  The Georgian party handed over lists of 870 persons missing 
in military clashes in Abkhazia. The Abkhazian representatives 
promised to assist in searching for them. 
  Both the parties exchanged specific data, addresses, 
surnames 
of missing persons and promises to inquire into each particular 
case. 
  The parties agreed to go ahead with cooperation in the 
field. 
  The Georgian delegation was led by Paat Zakareishvili, 
deputy 
chairman of the State Committee for Protection of Human Rights, 
the Abkhazian one - by Rezo Zantariya, deputy chairman of the 
State Commission on Exchange of Prisoners of War. 
  The Sochi-based Staff for Civil Defence and Emergencies 
contributed to organization of the meeting. 

</TEXT>

