<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition To Seek Supreme Court Ruling on CIS </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1403150794 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 12 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM1403150794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS report: "Georgian Parliamentary Opposition </F>
`Against' CIS Membership"] 
  [Text] The Georgian parliamentary opposition has given a 
hostile reception to the decision of the majority of the 
deputies on the republic's membership of the CIS. This decision 
has been perceived by the opposition as "support for Russia's 
imperial ambitions in the post-Soviet area." Deputies from the 
National Independence Party, the National Democratic Party, the 
People's Front, and a number of other parties (16 in all) are 
holding joint consultations and meetings to elaborate a policy 
of opposition to Georgia's inclusion in the CIS. 
  It has reached the stage where the opposition intends to 
appeal to the republic's Supreme Court because, in its opinion, 
parliament's decision on Georgia's membership of the CIS is 
unlawful. Its appeal is based on the fact that this decision 
was made by a simple majority of deputies and not two-thirds of 
them, even though the republic's legislation contains no clear 
ruling on that question. 

</TEXT>

