<H3> <TI>   Communists Lead S. Ossetian Election Campaign </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403194194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1746 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1403194194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Communist Party is leading in the pre-election 
campaign for a new parliament in South Ossetia, the 
self-proclaimed republic on the territory of Georgia, deputy 
chairman of the Central Electoral Commission Makhar Gasiyev told 
Interfax. He said 185 candidates have been registered for 41 
seats in a new parliament to be elected on March 27. 
  Gasiyev said opinion polls show that the Communist Party is 
supported by 90 percent of the South Ossetian population. 
"People are tired of the never-ending disorder." "People need 
to be protected, and they lay their hopes on the new 
parliament," Gaisyev said. 

</TEXT>

