<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tiimann `Ready' for Removal of Nuclear Fuel </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1403210494 Tallinn BNS in English 1329 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1403210494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, Mar 14, BNS -- Estonia is in every respect 
ready for the removal of nuclear fuel from Paldiski, Ago 
Tiimann, secretary of the Estonian delegation for talks with 
Russia and head of the military issues working group, told BNS. 
  Tiimann said the dismantling of the Paldiski reactors is the 
only military issue under discussion at the negotiations "on 
which (the delegations) have been working closely together." 
  "To date, everything has proceeded as planned and in 
accordance with agreements," Tiimann claimed. 
  Russia has more than once announced that it is prepared to 
start removal of nuclear fuel from Paldiski already in April and 
complete it by June. 
  Tiimann said all possible safety and security measures will 
be taken during the operation, which is the reason why the dates 
and the route will not be made public. 
  Russia plans to use for transporting the fuel new, TK-18 
type 
containers, which have never before been used for this purpose. 
The authorities are going to test the containers in March to 
find out if they meet safety standards. 

</TEXT>

