<H3> <TI>   Legislators Introduce Bill To Change Election Law </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1403211194 Tallinn ETA in English 1744 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1403211194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["News Release"] </F>
  [Text] Tallinn, March 14 -- Twenty seven MPs on Monday [14 
March] presented the parliament a bill on amendments to 
Estonia's Constitution to change the current election law under 
which the president is elected by the parliament if none of the 
candidates receives the majority of votes at presidential 
elections. 
  Under the bill, the two candidates who have gathered most 
votes would compete for the position in the second round of 
elections two weeks after the first round. 

</TEXT>

