<F P=100> BALTIC STATES </F>
<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Decreases Ostankino Transmission Time </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1103203594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1920 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1103203594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Estonian Government decided to cut down the 
transmission time of the Russian TV broadcasting company 
Ostankino on the territory of the republic from 9.5 to 4 hours a 
day starting on March 11, Government Press Secretary Ain Saarna 
told a briefing in Tallinn Friday [11 March]. He said the only 
Russian channel in Estonia will be broadcast every day from 
18:00 to 22:00. 
  Saarna explained the measure by saying that Russia owed 
about 
DM [German marks] 200,000 to Estonian Esttelecommunications for 
relaying the broadcasts. 
  The Estonian government asked Esttelecommunications to 
inform 
Ostankino of its decision and to conclude a new contract 
envisioning the reimbursement of its debt and regulating other 
procedural issues before March 28. Otherwise, Ostankino 
programs will no longer be broadcast on Estonian territory, 
Saarna said. 

</TEXT>

