<H3> <TI>   Arrives in Sochi </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503091894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0735 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1503091894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Sochi March 15 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin, who arrived in Sochi on Monday on a brief vacation, on 
the same day met with the regional head of the Krasnodar region, 
Nikolay Yegorov. The two discussed a wide range of economic, 
political and management issues. 
  Before departure from Moscow Yeltsin told journalists that 
he 
is going to Sochi "in order to work there, rather than for 
medical treatment." In particular, during his vacation the 
president intends to work out a mechanism of the realisation of 
the presidential message to the Federal Assembly and consider 
the problem of preparations for a draft agreement on civil peace 
and accord. 

</TEXT>

