Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [POSTFACTUM report: "Federal Counterintelligence Service </F>
Director Sergey Stepashin Hospitalized"] 
  [Text] Lieutenant General Sergey Stepashin, Federal 
Counterintelligence Service director, was taken to the hospital 
in an ambulance from his own office after, according to some 
information, becoming sick due to a worsening of his stomach 
ulcer. The confidential source, who would rather remain 
anonymous, intimated that the reason was not the illness but the 
meeting with President Yeltsin, soon after which Sergey 
Stepashin was sent to the departmental hospital. 

