<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows Majority Consider Amnesty Wrong </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1503085594 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 12 Mar 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM1503085594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "`Opinion' of the Amnesty"] </F>
  [Text] The "Opinion" service (leader Gr. Pashkov) carried 
out a telephone poll 4-6 March. There were 1,100 respondents. 
The sample is representative in terms of sex, age, level of 
education, and main types of work: 
  Do you think that the State Duma acted rightly or wrongly in 
declaring an amnesty for those who participated in the events of 
August 1991 and October 1993? 
  Wrongly -- 56.9 
  Don't know -- 21.8 
  Do you think that following the amnesty the political 
situation in our country will improve, deteriorate, or stay the 
same? 
  Improve -- 6.1 
  Deteriorate -- 43.6 
  Stay the same -- 28.2 
  Don't know -- 22.1 
  What punishment do you think 1) the members of the State 
Committee for the State of Emergency, 2) Rutskoy, and 3) 
Khasbulatov, deserve? 


