<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Soskovets Holds News Conference on Reform Moves </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403145894 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1100 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1403145894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [T. Aldoshina report; from the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The government is apparently to get involved in 
solving the problems of reciprocal nonpayments between 
enterprises. [First Deputy Prime Minister] Oleg Soskovets 
announced at a news conference today that this is really a 
problem for enterprise managers to resolve. The first deputy 
prime minister is of the view that nonpayments are the result of 
poor management and badly organized relations between suppliers 
and consumers. 
  As for the wage arrears in a number of industries, the 
Ministry of Labor has been instructed to investigate and to take 
measures. Soskovets reiterated that the government intends to 
strengthen the role of the state in economic development. It is 
not yet clear how this will look in practice, as Oleg Soskovets 
was not inclined to talk specifics. He answered questions with 
either platitudes or statements such as: The government is 
studying this problem, or the government is working on this. 
  Incidentally, Soskovets' meeting with journalists today was 
the first of a series of news conferences on the implentation of 
the program of economic reforms in the period up to 1995. We 
will probably hear specific answers to all issues later. 

</TEXT>

