<H3> <TI>   Cites Budget Priorities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403194094 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1700 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1403194094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Video report by correspondent T. Aldoshina; from the </F>
"Vesti" newscast] 
  [Text] [Correspondent T. Aldoshina] Today, Oleg Soskovets 
held a news conference on the results of the government's 
extended session. He said that the main directions of the 
country's development have been indicated in the president's 
message. The first deputy prime minister named the following 
among priority areas in the economy: The fuel and power complex, 
industry, agriculture, conversion, and restructuring of the 
social sphere. Commenting on information by Yegor Gaydar that 
the draft budget provides for an increase in expenditure on the 
upkeep of the state apparatus and not for social needs, Oleg 
Soskovets said: 
  [Begin recording] [Soskovets] It is the normal thing that 
when the state apparatus increases, the social sphere is reduced. 
  [Aldoshina] But still, precisely this situation is set out 
in 
the draft budget, isn't it? 
  [Soskovets] We have not yet put out the draft budget 
anywhere. [end recording] 
  [Aldoshina] The draft budget, according to the first deputy 
prime minister, may be passed on to the State Duma this week. 
Commenting on the question of Gaydar's intention to return to 
the government, Oleg Soskovets said: That is his problem. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

