<H3> <TI>   Ministry Cuts Off RTV Video Feed Channels </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503113594 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
0400 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1503113594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] We have some urgent problems here on Russian TV 
today. For example, today the Ministry of Communications is 
cutting us off from all channels of transmission of video 
material from other cities and countries. Yes, talking 
on-screen for 20 minutes is not one of the easiest tasks for a 
newscaster. It seems that Russians will have to do without 
bright pictures as well as having to do without good-quality 
bread. Well, that's enough gloomy news; we do have something to 
boast about: We are the national TV station. 

</TEXT>

