<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Meets Krasnodar Kray Head </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503111394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0946 
GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1503111394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Excerpt] Sochi, 15 Mar (ITAR-TASS) -- Russian President 
Boris Yeltsin, who arrived in Sochi on Monday on a brief 
vacation, met with Nikolay Yegorov, head of Krasnodar Kray, the 
same day. 
  Nikolay Yegorov told an ITAR-TASS correspondent that the 
president showed that he is very well informed about business 
and political life in the Kuban. He enquired about the course 
of spring field work, and the provision of Russia's breadbasket 
with fuel, mineral fertilizers, and other material and technical 
resources on the eve of the new sowing campaign. 
  Nikolay Yegorov said that the president paid particular 
attention to discussing the problems of Krasnodar Kray as a 
territory on Russia's southern border. Issues of the migration 
of the population from CIS "trouble spots" were discussed. The 
president agreed with the proposal by the kray's leadership 
temporarily to introduce a visa regime on the territory of 
Krasnodar Kray while the acute situations in the Transcaucasus 
region continue. Nikolay Yegorov said that the Russian 
leadership will apparently adopt an appropriate document on this 
matter very soon. 
  The conversation lasted about five hours. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

