<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tatarstan Nationalists Attack Federal Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403171394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1406 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1403171394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An alliance of nationalist groups in Tatarstan in a 
letter to the Central Election Commission in Moscow on Monday 
have protested against yesterday's elections to the Federal 
Assembly in the republic. They described the vote as 
unconstitutional and as a gross violation of human rights and 
the Tatars' right to self-determination. "The election has 
brought the republic on the brink of civil war", it says. 
  Leaders of the umbrella organization including the Tatar 
Public Center, Ittifak Party and Azatlyk Youth Movement are 
challenging the voting results because of what they saw as a ban 
on opposition meetings and rallies in the election campaign. 
The letter speaks of a government-sponsored campaign of 
intimidation and threats of dismissals and non-payment of wages 
in urban areas and withdrawal of subsidies in the countryside. 
  They accused the government of imposing censorship of the 
mass media and barring representatives of the nationalist groups 
from monitoring the election. 
  The authors of the letter say they have appealed for 
international inquiry into the legitimacy of federal elections 
in Tatarstan and an anti-democratic environment in which they 
were held. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

