<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Accord on Border Troops Signed With Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503121694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1129 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1503121694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tigran Liloyan] </F>
  [Text] Yerevan March 15 TASS -- "The presence of the 
Russian border troops in the Transcaucasus on the basis of an 
agreement with Georgia and Armenia points to the recognition of 
Russia's strategic interests in this region," the Commander in 
Chief of the Russian Border Troops General Andrey Nikolayev said 
here today. 
  On behalf of the Russian president he signed an agreement on 
the enlistment and service of Armenian citizens in Russia's 
border troops stationed on the territory of this republic. 
  Russia and Armenia also signed bilateral protocol on the 
text 
of the oath to be taken when joining the Russian border troops. 
  Both the agreement and the protocol are of extremely great 
importance, General Nikolayev told ITAR-TASS. They practically 
complete a series of documents relating to the presence of 
Russian border troops on Armenian territory and on cooperation 
between the two countries in protecting the state border. 
  We have completed all steps connected with the preparation 
of 
the necessary legal basis, from the status of presence to the 
system of manning borderguard units and funding provisions for 
them, the general said. 
  General Nikolayev stressed the importance of this 
accomplishment for Russian border guards and Armenian citizens. 

</TEXT>

