<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Supreme Soviet Passes New Constitution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503132794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1154 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1503132794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Belinform correspondent for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Minsk March 15 TASS -- The Belarusian Supreme Soviet 
legislature passed on Tuesday a new constitution. 
  Under the new constitution, Belarus is to become a 
presidential republic. It is declared "a unitary democratic 
social law-governed state", with man regarded as the highest 
value of society and the state. 
  Belarus sets the goal of becoming a nuclear-free and neutral 
power. 
  The republic's president will also be the head of the 
executive branch. The parliament is to be reduced to 260 
deputies from the present 360 lawmakers. It will remain 
semi-professional, that is part of deputies will work full-time 
in the parliament's standing commissions, while the rest will 
combine their deputy's posts with some other jobs. 
  The parliament ruled that presidential elections should be 
called before this July, while elections to a new parliament are 
to be held not later than this year. 
  The new fundamental law of the Republic of Belarus is to 
come 
into force from the date of its publication. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-16301 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov050_c_94001" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-050 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
