<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fourth Round of Talks With European Union Begins </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1503100194 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 0600 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1503100194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The fourth round of negotiations between Ukraine and 
the European Union [EU] on concluding a treaty on partnership 
and cooperation began yesterday at the EU headquarters. 
Assessing the first day of the talks, Ukrainian Deputy Foreign 
Minister Oleksandr Makarenko, head of the Ukrainian delegation, 
noted that they were held in an atmosphere of constructiveness 
and mutual understanding. If the negotiations conclude with the 
results expected by both sides, Ukraine will be the first CIS 
state to conclude such a treaty with the EU. 

</TEXT>

