<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Assesses Reorganization </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503003494 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
2000 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1503003494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A news conference on the results of the Cabinet of 
Ministers sitting, chaired by Ukraine's President Leonid 
Kravchuk, was held on 14 March in Kiev. As was pointed out at 
the meeting with journalists, the consideration of the draft 
program of structural reorganization of Ukraine's economy was 
[word indistinct] at the sitting. Deputy Minister of Economy 
Leonid Minin stressed at the news conference that this document 
received, in general, a positive assessment at the sitting. It 
will be submitted for the consideration of the Supreme Council. 
It is a conceptual basis for Ukraine's transition toward market 
principles of economic management with social orientation and 
its integration into the world system of labor distribution with 
regard to the specific nature of our state's economic 
development. The draft envisages the urgent overcoming of 
emission and hyperinflation and measures to accelerate the 
privatization processes. 
  Also, a report by President Leonid Kravchuk on the results 
of 
the official visit by Ukraine's state delegation to Washington 
was heard at the sitting. Judging from the agreements achieved 
there, they managed to bring Ukrainian-American relations to a 
qualitatively new level. In particular, a large-scale program 
of economic and other cooperation between the two countries was 
mapped out. First and foremost, this is manifested in the fact 
that the United States is ready to grant 2.5 million dollars in 
aid for the implementation of about 70 specific projects. 

</TEXT>

