<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Slow Progress in Russian-Latvian Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403170894 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1400 GMT 14 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1403170894 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] [Announcer] As has already been reported, Latvian- 
Russian interstate talks resumed in Moscow today. Ritums 
Rozenbergs, Latvian Radio Moscow correspondent and the LABRIT 
newspaper, will tell us more. 
  [Rozenbergs] This morning, the Latvian and Russian 
delegations considered texts of the agreement. The delegations 
agreed that additional consultations were needed on certain 
issues. As a result of the meeting held this morning, both the 
Russian and Latvian sides hope that the social security issue 
for Russian military pensioners will be tackled. However, 
findings of banks' experts are needed in order to reach this 
agreement. So then, it is necessary to clarify the mechanism of 
the payment of pensions. 
  On the issue of the Skrunda military base the delegations 
decided at the morning meeting that the text of the agreement 
would be acceptable for both sides. The Russian delegation has 
not yet given final consent in connection with the fact that a 
rent payment of 400 million dollars a year, demanded by the 
Latvian side, is under question. The Latvian side expresses the 
wish that several agreements favorable to Latvia could be 
reached. 
  Ritums Rozenbergs, special Moscow correspondent of the 
LABRIT 
newspaper, specially for Latvian radio. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

