<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Cancels Meeting With Japanese Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503123794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1051 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1503123794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vyacheslav Bantin] </F>
  [Text] Tokyo March 15 TASS -- The expected meeting between 
Japan's Minister of Foreign Affairs Tsutomu Hata and Russian 
President Boris Yeltsin has been cancelled, Kyodo TSUSHIN news 
agency reported today, citing source in the Japanese Foreign 
Ministry. 
  Tsutomu Hata, who arrives in Moscow on March 19, will hold 
talks with Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin and 
Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev. 
  Boris Yeltsin will be unable to receive the Japanese 
minister, because he is out of Moscow for a vacation in the 
Black Sea coast resort of Sochi. 

