<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lipetsk Voters `Boycotted' Oblast Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1503090194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 12 Mar 94 
First Edition p 2 </F>

<F P=103> PM1503090194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Correspondent Viktor Metchikov report under "Regional </F>
Elections" rubric: "Lipetsk Boycotts Elections"] 
  [Text] Lipetsk -- A total of only 19 deputies in 38 
districts were elected to Lipetsk Oblast Deputies' Assembly in 
the elections held last Sunday [13 March]. Although the 
elections have been officially declared valid because the 
statute on this organ of representative power adopted by the 
oblast soviet enables it to start work with any quorum, the 
assembly's viability with only half its members seems extremely 
doubtful. 
  Even in rural districts the voter turnout has sharply 
decreased. As regards the city, it can be said that Lipetsk 
boycotted the elections en masse. Because of the low turnout of 
city inhabitants at polling stations (between 11 and 24 
percent), they were not valid in a single one of the oblast 
center's districts. Not a single deputy was elected to the city 
organ of representative power. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

