<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Supreme Soviet Adopts New Constitution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1503142994 Minsk BELAPAN in Belarusian 1300 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1503142994 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk BELAPAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 15 March, the Belarusian Supreme Soviet adopted 
the new Belarusian Constitution with 236 "yes" votes, six "no" 
votes, and eight abstentions. The major innovation of the 
Constitution is that the presidential form of governing is 
outlined. It is expected that the election of the first 
Belarusian president will take place on 26 June 1994. The final 
"touch" added by the Supreme Soviet was an amendment to Article 
49 of the Constitution, which guarantees broad and free access 
to secondary and vocational education in the Republic. The new 
Constitution will come into force immediately after it is 
published in the Belarusian press. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

