<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Church: Media `Irresponsibly' Misleads Public </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1503151994 Tallinn BNS in English 1331 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1503151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, Mar 15, BNS -- The Episcopal Conference of 
Lithuania, the highest governing body of the Lithuanian Catholic 
Church, expressed regret about "how irresponsibly the press, 
radio and television use freedom and mislead the public." 
  In a statement circulated Tuesday [15 March], the conference 
said Lithuania is flooded with various religious cults and sects 
that "reject the teaching of the Christian Church, disseminate 
the ideas and superstitions of `the new age,' which are 
extremely dangerous to those who do not have deep Christian 
fundamentals. 
  "We regret that even priests sometimes irresponsibly use 
public communication means and spread ideas that cannot be 
reconciled with the Christian doctrine." The statement mentions 
a case when a priest on television spoke about contacts with 
extraterrestrials. 
  The Episcopal Conference urged media sources to be more 
responsible and not to dig up sensations about "travels in 
space" and other miracles, "which deliberately or 
unintentionally ruin the true faith and contradict the teaching 
of the Church." 

</TEXT>

