<F P=102>  WS1503204994 Vilnius ELTA in English 1812 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1503204994 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius ELTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "News Bulletin" No. 457] </F>
  [Text] Vilnius, March 15, ELTA -- On Tuesday the 
subscribers of the newspaper VALSTIECIU LAIKRASTIS received the 
issue with blank pages with the statement of its staff on them. 
This was the protest of the editorial staff of the newspaper 
against the attempts of Labour Democrats to seize the 
independent newspaper. 
  The editorial staff stated that "radical group of Labour 
Democrats suggested to the Government stopping the activities of 
our joint-stock company by seizing its property and shares and 
throwing us out or making their servants". 
  On Tuesday Labour Democrats also publicized their comments 
on 
the action and stated that "the action of the newspaper is not 
original. In 1991 four main Lithuanian dailies launched similar 
action in protest against attempts of Landbergis and Vagnorius 
Government to nationalize them. The journalists' protest was 
not taken into consideration and the VALSTIECIU LAIKRASTIS was 
made dependent on supporters of Landsbergis". 
  The statement also said that "Labour Democrats are not going 
to repeat the methods used by Vagnorius and will try to 
establish the justice in court." 

</TEXT>

