Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Nikolay Morozov] </F>
  [Text] Bucharest, 15 Mar TASS -- Ukraine plans to have 
friendly relations with Romania and settle all problems in a 
political way, Ukrainian Defence Minister Army General Vitaliy 
Radetskyy said today upon his arrival in Bucharest with a 
Ukrainian military delegation at the invitation of the Romanian 
defence minister. 
  The visit to last till 17 March includes negotiations with 
Romanian Defence Minister Gheorghe Tinca, head of the Romanian 
Armed Forces General Staff Lieutenant-General Dumitru Cioflina 
and meetings with President Ion Iliescu, Prime Minister Nicolae 
Vacaroiu and Foreign Minister Teodor Melescanu. 
  The sides are expected to sign a military cooperation 
agreement. 
  "We had long planned to sign a bilateral accord on military 
cooperation, especially as we have a border running over 600 
kilometers (375 miles) with Romania," said the Ukrainian 
official. "The agreement will help military interaction, 
including joint training of personnel." 

