<F P=102>  PM1603095594 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 16 Mar 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM1603095594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report from roundup of ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA and ITAR-TASS </F>
reports: "He Will Not Run for President"] 
  [Text] "I do not intend to run for the post of the 
country's president even if I am asked." That was the position 
voiced by Moscow Mayor Yuriy Luzhkov. 
  Yuriy Luzhkov denied the press' numerous claims that he 
created the Party of the Majority for his future election 
campaign. "I have nothing to do with it except for the fact 
that at the request of one of my friends I signed greetings to 
the constitutent congress of the Party of the Majority sinces 
its aim -- supporting the establishment of a class of 
entrepreneurs -- does not contradict my views," our interlocutor 
explained. 

