<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Says Party Favors Economic Stability </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503135594 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1100 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1503135594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By S. Sokolova; from the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Representatives of the Liberal Democratic Party 
[LDP] met with leaders of Russian and foreign banks in the 
Parliamentary Center today. Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, leader of 
the party, emphasized that the Liberal Democrats today are in 
favor of economic stability in Russia and the development of 
private entrepreneurship, and that they will put through 
parliament a number of laws that will help Russian banks to work 
normally. He also reported that the country is now entering a 
new stage of political construction, and if the communists are 
allowed to come to power Russia could plunge into ruin, that is, 
there would be no healthy capitalism and private banks. Yet if 
the rudder passes to Russia's Choice, all Russian money will 
rapidly go to the West. 
  After some eulogistic speeches were made about his party, 
Zhirinovskiy complained about the government, which in their 
opinion has still not collected the taxes for 1993 and has not 
confirmed in the State Duma the budget for 1994. 

</TEXT>

