<F P=101> Media Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Warns TV, Radio Broadcast Cuts `Possible' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1603133694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1144 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1603133694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In the near term the amount of TV and radio 
broadcasting will not be reduced as it was on February 10, 
"however, in general such an action is quite possible," Chairman 
of the Central Committee of the Trade Union of 
Telecommunications Workers Anatoly Nazeikin declared to INTERFAX 
on Wednesday while commenting on related TV stories. 
  He also reported that since the beginning of this year 
analogical problems appeared among telecommunications employees 
who only now received payment for last year's debts for 
broadcasting of state TV and radio programs. In addition, 
agreements with TV and radio companies have not been concluded 
yet because the quantity of broadcasting to be done is as yet 
unknown. 
  Nazeikin underlined that the issues concerning mutual 
payments between collectives of broadcasting centers and TV and 
radio companies were to be solved in the course of the meeting 
between representatives of telecommunications workers and Prime 
Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin scheduled "for the near term." 
However, this meeting has not taken place. If this continues 
till the end of March, Nazeikin continued, we shall be forced to 
cut back TV and radio broadcasting time for the majority of 
Russia's regions. (On February 10 broadcasting was limited in 61 
regions -- INTERFAX). 

</TEXT>

