<H3> <TI>   Yerin Unveils R2 Trillion Crime Fighting Program </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK1603102094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 16 Mar 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK1603102094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Aleksandr Barinov report under the "In Brief" rubric: "Two </F>
Trillion for Fighting Crime"] 
  [Text] A federal crime fighting program for 1994 and 1995 
has been formed and a presidential edict for its approval is now 
in the works. This was announced by Viktor Yerin, head of the 
Russian Ministry of Internal Affairs, at a scheduled news 
briefing there yesterday. According to the minister, this 
program has been elaborated on Boris Yeltsin's personal 
instructions with all Russian ministries and agencies taking 
part in putting it together. In Mr. Yerin's words, it has a 
fundamentally new nature, and it is not going to end up in 
mid-air, as has happened more than once. The program is to be 
financed mainly by ministries and agencies (with virtually all 
taking part in it), each taking care of its own sphere. All in 
all nearly 2 trillion rubles at current prices would be required 
to implement it. 

</TEXT>

