<F P=101> Military &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Work Aboard Mir Space Station Continues </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503164494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1311 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1503164494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Flight Control Centre (Moscow Region), March 15 
(TASS) -- The crew of the 15th main expedition continues its 
mission aboard the Mir space station. 
  The cosmonauts refuelled on March 14 the joint power pack of 
the station with an oxidizer from tanks of the progress M-21 
ferry. They will refuel it with the second fuel component on 
Tuesday. 
  The programme for today also includes measurements of soft 
gamma radiation in near-earth space as well as technological 
experiments. 
  Work will continue under the international "Rentgen" 
programme for astrophysical explorations. Using telescopes of 
the orbital obvservatory at the "Kvant" module, the crew plans 
to investigate roentgen sources in the centre of our galaxy. 
  According to the results of medical checkups, Viktor 
Afanasyev, Yuriy Usachyov and Valeriy Polyakov are healthy and 
feel well. 

</TEXT>

