<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials Comment on Recognition of Karabakh </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1503195894 Baku TURAN in English 1650 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1503195894 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku (March 15) TURAN--Armenian Speaker of 
Parliament, Babken Ararktsyan said yesterday in Yerevan that 
during the course of his meeting with Rasul Guliyev on March 12 
at the Azero-Armenian border, the both sides agreed that the 
Upper Karabakh [Nagorno-Karabakh] representatives must have full 
participation in all talks. 
  According to Ararktsyan, the Azerbaijani side agreed that 
"the Lachin humanitarian corridor between Armenia and Karabakh 
must exist." 
  After the meeting with Ararktsyan in Kazakhskiy, Rasul 
Guliyev said that Azerbaijan categorically will recognize the 
so-called Karabakh Republic. However, the head of the 
department dealing with ethnic conflicts and political 
settlement of the Armenian-Azeri conflict of the Ministry of the 
Foreign Affairs, Tofik Zulfugarov, told Turan agency that "We 
recognize them (the Karabakh Armenians) as representatives of 
the Armenian community, not in the form of any state. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-16377 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov051_r_94002" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-051 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  15 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Party Officials Comment on Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1503192094 Baku TURAN in English 1650 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1503192094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku (MARCH 15) TURAN--"At the present situation, 
the ceasefire is necessary for Azerbaijan, because Azerbaijan 
needs a respite", said Zardusht Alizade, the Azerbaijani Social 
Democratic Party's Central Committee member commenting on the 
results of the talks between parliament leaders of Azerbaijan 
and Armenia. 
  According to Alizade, the actual outcome of the agreements 
and the negotiation process will depend mostly on the Russias 
position. 
  Touching on the question about the status of Upper Karabakh 
[Nagorno-Karabakh] Alizade said, "We support the idea of giving 
the status of autonomy to Upper Karabakh...in fact, Armenian 
civilians do not live there, for the most part... [ellipses as 
received] Since the ethnic cleansing of Azeris from that 
territory, fascist-military control was established in Upper 
Karabakh." He also noted that the autonomy does not pose a 
threat to the integrity and sovereignty of Azerbaijan. "It does 
not mean that federalisation of the republic will take place; 
Azerbaijan will remain a united republic", he added. 
  The Azerbaijani National Independence Party's leader, Etibar 
Mamedov, said that he was not yet acquainted with the results of 
the talks. 
  "I am not yet aware the concrete conditions of the 
agreement. 
One thing is known. The Armenian party has demanded to a 
guarantee prior to its withdrawal. If they mean that this 
guarantee includes the deployment of the Russian army in the 
territory, we are categorically against that and we shall not 
give them such an opportunity", said Etibar Mamedov. In his 
opinion, "one country cannot solve this problem as a mediator. 
Moreover, Russia has its own interests in this matter." 
  According to Mamedov, the question of autonomy of 
Nagorno-Karabakh could be solved on the basis of international 
norms, i.e. on the level of self-governance without the 
representation of a state. "It is impossible to have a state in 
the state", noted he. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

