<H3> <TI>   Official Warns No More Concessions to Crimea Separatists </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503223494 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 2040 GMT 15 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1503223494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow 2x2 Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mykola Mykhalchenko, head of the Ukrainian 
president's Internal Policy Service, stated today in a national 
radio interview that Kiev can no longer make concessions to 
separatists in Crimea. Their games could lead to an Abkhaz-style 
development of events. It is better to stop the separatists now 
than to establish order by military force later, he said. 

</TEXT>

