<H3> <TI>   Naval Commander Rules Out Giving Fleet to Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1503161994 Kiev MOLOD UKRAYINY in Ukrainian 11 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU1503161994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev MOLOD UKRAYINY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report published under the rubric "Fact"] </F>
  [Text] In an interview for the foreign press, the 
commander of Ukraine's Naval Forces, Volodymyr Bezkorovaynyy, 
said that our state does not consider the possibility of 
transferring its part of the Black Sea Fleet ships to Russia to 
repay the debt for oil and gas deliveries. The commander of 
Ukraine's Naval Forces said that the protocol signed in 
Massandra [in the Crimea] was a protocol on intentions. It was 
never regarded as a way out of the situation. According to 
Volodymyr Bezkorovaynyy, that question was studied and rejected. 

