<H3> <TI>   Meri Affirms 1921 Agreement With Ukraine Valid </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1603111494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1100 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1603111494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Yefim Shvartsman] </F>
  [Text] Kiev March 16 TASS -- "Estonia intends to develop 
relations with Ukraine on the basis of their 1921 agreement, 
which we consider valid", Estonian President Lennart Meri told 
journalists at Kiev Airport upon arriving for a visit to Kiev. 
According to him, that document still has legal force. 
  The Estonian president expects his visit to mark the 
beginning of a closer cooperation between the two states in 
politics, economy and culture. 

