<H3> <TI>   Government Discusses `Temporary' Travel Documents </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1503205494 Tallinn ETA in English 1916 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1503205494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["News Release"] </F>
  [Text] Tallinn, March 15 -- Minister of Justice Kaido Kama 
told a news conference that Estonian Government discussed, at 
its Tuesday [15 March] meeting, the order of issuing temporary 
travel documents to foreigners living in Estonia. 
  He said that temporary travel documents are issued to 
persons 
that do not need a foreigners passport indispensably but who 
need to travel abroad for a shorter or a longer period. He 
added that Foreign Ministry was holding talks, at present, with 
other states on which form of the temporary travel documents 
would be acceptable and how visas could be stamped in them. 
  Kama said that the final decision on temporary travel 
documents will be made by the government when solution to the 
problems of issuing foreigners passports is found. 

</TEXT>

