<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Submits Bill Outlining State Secrets </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1503205394 Tallinn ETA in English 1916 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1503205394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["News Release"] </F>
  [Text] Tallinn, March 15 -- Estonian Government, on 
Tuesday [15 March], sent law on state secrets, defining the 
regulations on pieces of information, declared a state secret, 
to the Riigikogu [parliament], Minister of Justice Kaido Kama 
told a press conference. 
  Kama said that the bill defines also areas on which 
information cannot be concealed e.g. information on emergency 
cases, nature catastrophes, information concerning ecological 
and demographic situation. 
  Government will appoint an expert working group that will 
propose which information to consider a state secret. If the 
proposition is adopted, defence of the secrets will be carried 
out by the Defence Police Department. 

</TEXT>

