<H3> <TI>   Official on Border Agreement With Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1503215194 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 2000 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1503215194 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 2000 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Armenian Vice President Gagik Arutyunyan today 
received General Andrey Nikolayev, commander in chief of Russian 
border troops. 
  The Armenian presidential press service reported that the 
Armenian vice president and the commander in chief of the border 
troops examined matters relating to the joint defense of state 
borders. They specifically discussed the enlistment of Armenian 
citizens in military service in the Russian border guard units 
stationed in Armenia, the joint defense of borders, and matters 
pertaining to legal procedures regulating the joint defense of 
the borders. 
  Armenian Prime Minister Grant Bagratyan today also received 
General Andrey Nikolayev, commander in chief of Russian border 
troops. The prime minister stressed the importance of the 
signed documents on the enlistment of Armenian citizens in the 
Russian border troops and considered it a significant step in 
the development of Armenian-Russian cooperation. 
  Matters relating to the joint defense of Armenia's state 
borders, including the financial, economic, and technical 
aspects, were discussed during the meeting. 
  Vazgen Sargisyan [Armenian state minister and commander of 
border guards] and Andrey Nikolayev signed an agreement at noon 
today. You can hear the details in Gevorg Nazaryan's report: 
  [Begin recording] [Nazaryan] An agreement was signed today 
on 
the enlistment of Armenian citizens in the Russian border guard 
units stationed in Armenia and on regulations on military 
service. It was signed by General Andrey Nikolayev, commander in 
chief of Russian border troops, and Armenian State Minister 
Vazgen Sargisyan. 
  This is how the signatories assessed the document after the 
signing ceremony. Let us first hear Andrey Nikolayev. [passage 
omitted] 
  Now let us hear State Minister Vazgen Sargisyan. 
  [Sargisyan] This is a very important agreement, especially 
for the soldiers who are currently serving on the borders, for 
the Armenian and Russian soldiers who are jointly defending 
Armenia's and, in effect, CIS' borders. The soldiers were 
waiting for it. This agreement will greatly facilitate their 
service and clarify what we and Russia should be doing. 
Therefore, it is highly important. 
  [Nazaryan] Let me add that Russian Ambassador to Armenia 
Vladimir Stupishin; Davit Shahnazaryan, the Armenian president's 
ambassador on special missions and acting head of the State 
Directorate for National Security of the Armenian Republic; and 
other officials were present at the signing ceremony. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

