<H3> <TI>   Karabakh Official on Armenian-Azerbaijani Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1503192794 Yerevan SNARK in English 1128 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1503192794 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Stepanakert, March 15 (SNARK)--Karen Baburyan, 
acting as a Chairman of the Karabakh Supreme Soviet, told 
journalists at his press-conference in Stepanakert neither any 
decisions nor the concrete plans on the Karabakh conflict 
regulation could be realized without participation of the 
Karabakh side. 
  Thus, Mr. Baburyan considers the mass media statements on 
the 
agreement on the Karabakh troops withdrawal within the period of 
20 days, as groundless ones. Mass media reported on the fact 
that the agreement was as if achieved as a result of the recent 
meeting of Babken Ararktsyan, a Chairman of the Armenian 
Parliament, and Rasul Guliyev, a Chairman of the Azerbaijani 
Milli Majlis. 
  According to the information the Karabakh side possesses, 
Mr. 
Chairman said, there were discussed ways of the 
Armenian-Azerbaijani relations. No concrete treaty was 
concluded. 

</TEXT>

