<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Federation Council Approves 1994 Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503161694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1345 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1503161694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anna Melnikova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow March 15 TASS -- The Russian Parliament's 
Upper House, the Federation Council, approved at today's session 
a plan for legislative initiatives for the first six months of 
1994. The plan provides for 19 bills to be drafted and 
submitted for the consideration of the state duma, the 
parliament's lower house. 
  The bills on the list include several draft laws worked out 
on the basis of provisions of the presidential message to the 
Federal Assembly. These are a draft law "On Russia's Free 
Economic Zones", "On Participation of Russian Military 
Contingents in Peacekeeping Missions, Including Within the CIS, 
CSCE and UN Framework", "On International Treaties of the 
Russian Federation", On the Status of Foreigners in Russia, and 
"On Higher and Post-Graduate Professional Education". 
  The Federation Council also suggests drafting laws "on 
Federal Bodies of State Power", "On a Procedure for 
Implementation of the Federative Treaty and Delimitation of 
Powers", "Basic Principles of Legislation on Veterans", "On 
Federated Arrangement of the Russian Federation", and "On the 
Status of a Subject of the Russian Federation". 
  Addressing the gathering with a report, the House's First 
Deputy Speaker Ramazan Abdulatipov proposed setting up a 
scientific coordinating body to coordinate legislative 
activities by both chambers of the Russian Parliament. 
  The Federation Council passed a resolution saying it would 
resume discussing the plan of legislative initiatives after the 
state duma approved an analogous document. 

</TEXT>

