<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vladivostok Talks Part of `Mature Partnership' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1503160394 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 15 Mar 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM1503160394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "From Position of Mature Partnership"] </F>
  [Excerpt] Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev stated 
his intention of conducting his present talks in Vladivostok 
with U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher "from the 
position of a mature strategic partnership." 
  During the meeting that started in the Vladivostok Airport 
building straight after the official welcome ceremony for Warren 
Christopher, the heads of the Russian and U.S. foreign policy 
departments plan to discuss a brpad range of political, 
economic, and other issues. 
  In turn U.S Secretary of State Warren Christopher said at a 
press conference in Beijing before leaving for Vladivostok that 
consultations and coordination between Russia and the United 
States are extremely desirable. 
  With regard to the statements that "Russia is unhappy about 
being regarded as a junior partner," Christopher stressed that 
"Kozyrev has never said that to me. We are partners in our 
desire for reforms and support for reformers in Russia. And we 
will discuss these issues." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

