<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Returns From Vladivostok, Dushanbe </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503220394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2150 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1503220394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Andrey Sitov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow March 16 TASS -- Russian Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev returned to Moscow on Friday night upon the 
completion of his trip to Vladivostok and Dushanbe. 
  When in the Far East, the minister met U.S. State Secretary 
Warren Christopher to discuss a broad range of international 
issues and bilateral relations, and when in Tajikistan he met 
foreign ministers from Central Asia and Kazakhstan to discuss 
prospects for inter-Tajik political settlement. 
  Andrey Kozyrev also visited a warship of the Pacific Fleet 
and a border post at the Tajik-Afghan border. 

</TEXT>

