<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO Leader, Israeli Premier To Visit Moscow </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503165094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1625 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1503165094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Boris Krivoshey and </F>
Aleksandr Krylovich] 
  [Text] Moscow, March 15 (TASS) -- PLO leader Yasir 'Arafat 
will visit Moscow on April 19 and Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq 
Rabin will make a Moscow visit on April 24-26 at the invitation 
of President Yeltsin and under an agreement reached during the 
recent Tunisian and Israeli visits of Russian Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev, deputy director of the Russian Foreign 
Ministry's department for Middle East and Northern Africa Viktor 
Gogitidze told a briefing here today. 
  Estimating Kozyrev's trip, Gogitidze said that major tasks 
were fulfilled: An essential agreement of both sides was 
reached and PLO leader Yasir 'Arafat is ready to resume the 
negotiations. The Russian side is convinced both the Israelis 
and the Palestinians are adherent to the peace process and would 
like further talks. 
  "The Russian side stressed that in case of resumed dialogue 
the main attention should be given to the soonest completion of 
negotiations on the Gaza-Jericho project. Measures to implement 
the project should immediately follow," said the diplomat. In 
his opinion, "this would help to cool passions and guarantee, to 
a certain degree, security on the occupied lands". 
  Russia will take more efforts to achieve the soonest 
completion of negotiations on Gaza-Jericho and help the 
implementation of agreements, said Gogitidze. "Today's priority 
is the adoption of a Security Council resolution on Hebron. If 
the resolution is adopted there will be no obstacles for the 
resumption of Israeli-PLO negotiations," he stressed. 
  The settlers' problem that has grown most acute may be 
discussed "parallelly with the resumption of Israeli-PLO 
negotiations. A form of its solution can be found with the 
assistance of Russian diplomats, the co-sponsors and in direct 
contacts between Israel and the PLO," said Gogitidze. 

</TEXT>

