<H3> <TI>   Churkin Returns to Belgrade; Views Bosnia Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503223994 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
2020 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1503223994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Vitaliy Churkin has arrived in Belgrade after talks 
in Zagreb and Sarajevo. 
  [Begin Churkin recording] We do have some ideas how we can 
make further progress toward a political settlement, taking into 
account the latest developments, the advancement toward setting 
up a Muslim-Croatian federation. What concerns me, for example, 
is how the rights of the Serbs, who are one of the peoples 
making up the state, will be regarded and ensured in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, which should in our view be preserved as a 
territorial, integral state. Will they join the Muslim-Croatian 
federation which is currently being set up? It seems to me that 
it is of fundamental importance that Croatians and Muslims 
possess sovereign rights in Bosnia-Herzegovina. It should be 
obvious that the Serbs should have the same sovereign rights, 
too. [end recording] [Video shows Churkin being interviewed at 
airport] 

</TEXT>

