<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Welcomes Azeri-Armenian Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503175394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1708 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1503175394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Boris Krivoshey and </F>
Aleksandr Krylovich] 
  [Text] Moscow March 15 TASS -- Moscow Welcomes the March 12 
meeting of Azeri Parliament Speaker Rasul Guliyev and his 
Armenian counterpart Babken Ararktsyan, their essential 
agreements and striving to continue personal contacts, head of 
the Russian Foreign Ministry's Information and Press Department 
Grigoriy Karasin told a briefing here today. 
  Russia has always supported and encouraged direct conflicts 
between the warring sides on a realistic basis, he said 
[sentence as received]. 
  In the opinion of the diplomat, vague wordings of the 
cease-fire protocol resulted in close contact of the warring 
units and resumption of fighting. 
  Russia insistently continues mediating efforts and interacts 
with all states and international organizations interested in 
settlement of the Karabakh conflict, stressed the Foreign 
Ministry's spokesman. 

</TEXT>

