<H3> <TI>   Western Diplomats Hail Potential of Tatarstan Treaty </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1603095794 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 15 Mar 94 
First Edition p 6 </F>

<F P=103> PM1603095794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under "Contacts" rubric: "Visits by </F>
Diplomats"] 
  [Text] A number of Western countries' embassies in Moscow, 
having followed closely the development of relations between 
Tatarstan and Russia, sent their diplomats to the Permanent 
Mission of the Republic of Tatarstan in Moscow immediately after 
the signing of the bilateral treaty. 
  I.U. Yusupov, Tatarstan's permanent representative in 
Moscow, 
welcomed the following people for talks: M. Stross [name as 
transliterated], trade adviser to the French Embassy, and N. 
Shibayev [name as transliterated], this same embassy's adviser 
on political questions; Dr. Kh. Kretshmer [name as 
transliterated], EU deputy chief of mission; N. Foster, first 
secretary for political questions at the British Embassy; A. 
Ruigrok [name as transliterated], first secretary at the Dutch 
Embassy; and A. Hughes, second secretary at the South African 
Embassy. 
  During the meetings the diplomats expressed satisfaction at 
the conclusion of the treaty process and conveyed their 
congratulations to the Tatarstan leadership in the light of the 
treaty's signing. 
  Particular attention was paid during the talks to a 
discussion of this document's international-legal aspects, and 
above all the extensive opportunities the treaty opens up for 
participation in international organizations and the 
establishment and development of direct relations with foreign 
states, including for purposes of concluding agreements. 

