<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Meets With Nixon </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503145994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1406 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1503145994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow March 15 TASS -- Former U.S. President 
Richard Nixon met Tuesday with Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, leader of 
the Russian nationalist "Liberal Democratic" party. 
  The meeting was held behind closed doors. 
  The press service of Zhirinovskiy's party told ITAR-TASS 
that 
the two politicians focused on Russian-American relations 
"taking into consideration the geopolitical interests of the two 
countries", and on inter-parliamentary contacts. 
  Zhirinovskiy handed to Nixon a personal message addressed to 
President Bill Clinton, the press service said. 
  According to press reports, Nixon wanted to meet 
Zhirinovskiy 
during his week-long visit to Moscow to get a clearer idea of 
the broad spectrum of Russian political leaders capable of 
influencing developments in the country. 
  Zhirinovskiy, however, denied last week that he wanted to 
meet the American ex-president. 

</TEXT>

