<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Diplomat Views Plans for New COCOM </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503173894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1418 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1503173894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Vladivostok on Monday Andrey Kozyrev and U.S. 
Secretary of State Warren Christopher agreed that Russian 
experts would take part in drafting the project of a new COCOM. 
  A high-ranking Russian diplomat close to Kozyrev told 
INTERFAX that this was an extremely important aspect of 
Russian-American cooperation for the nonproliferation of 
missiles and other dangerous know-how. 
  "Suffice it to recall the incident involving the export of 
Russian cryogenic boosters to India and the restrictive moves of 
the West in relation to Russia, to understand how important this 
question is. The American side has understood at last that the 
nonproliferation of dangerous know-how is our common concern and 
treats Russia with more trust now," he said. 
  The fact that Russian experts will be involved in drafting 
the concept of a new COCOM from the very start is particularly 
important, he went on to say. They will not have to wait for 
what America will prepare for them, he added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

