<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Azerbaijan Delegation Attends </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1603214594 Baku Radio Baku International Service in Azeri 
1300 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1603214594 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Radio Baku International Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Azeri </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The CIS Council of Foreign Ministers and Council of 
Defense Ministers have convened in Moscow. Meanwhile, a 
delegation from Azerbaijan has arrived in that capital. Foreign 
Minister Gasan Gasanov and Defense Minister Mamedrafi Mamedov 
are among the members of the republic's delegation. 
  The Azerbaijan Ministry of Foreign Affairs Press Center told 
a Baku Radio correspondent that the CIS Council of Foreign 
Ministers is expected to deliberate on 11 matters related to the 
convention on the rights of national minorities, the agreement 
on collective security, territorial integrity of the CIS 
countries, mutual relations between the CIS and the CSCE, 
consultations among the CIS countries on the realization of the 
program for cooperation for peace, and other issues. 
  The republic's delegation intends to try to have the 
proposals Azerbaijan submitted during the CIS heads of state 
summit on collective security in Ashgabat on 24 December 
included in the agreement on collective security. Azerbaijan is 
convinced that the agreement's provisions must not only apply to 
foreign aggression against the CIS countries, but they must also 
apply to internal attacks. 
  The delegation plans to submit another document to the CIS 
Council of Foreign Ministers for approval by the CIS leaders. 
That is a draft declaration of respect for CIS members' 
sovereignty and territorial integrity and respect for the 
inviolability of their borders. The declaration notes that the 
principle of noninterference in each other's internal affairs 
must be the essence of friendly relations and cooperation among 
the CIS countries. 

</TEXT>

