<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Grachev Holds Talks With U.S. Defense Secretary </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1703110794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1017 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1703110794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Aleksey Agureyev and Vladimir </F>
Gondusov] 
  [Text] Moscow March 17 TASS -- Relations between the 
United States and Russia are the factor determining the degree 
of security in the whole world. This is why so much importance 
is being attached to contacts between the leaders of their 
defence authorities. This was the key idea behind today's 
meeting in Moscow between Russian Defence Minister Pavel Grachev 
and U.S. Defence Secretary William Perry. 
  A personal relationship between the two countries' defence 
ministers is no less important and need further deepening, the 
meeting was told. 
  Following talks between the two delegations, William Perry 
and Pavel Grachev are due to hold a one-to-one conversation. 
The Russian minister told journalists he wanted to discuss with 
his opposite number from the United States the situation in 
Bosnia, Russia's participation in the Partnership for Peace 
programme, joint peacekeeping, the problem of nuclear arms, 
including their withdrawal from Ukraine and a wide range of 
problems relating to better relations between the military 
authorities of the two countries. 
  Also today, William Perry is due to meet First Russian 
Deputy 
Defence Minister Andrey Kokoshin and Chief of Staff Mikhail 
Kolesnikov. 
  According to American sources, Perry, 66, is a true 
professional with deep knowledge and extensive experience. He 
favors the development of the Stealth bombers, Cruise missiles 
and high- precision electronic-optical homing devices. 

</TEXT>

