<H3> <TI>   Views `Partnership for Peace' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1703111694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1053 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1703111694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow March 17 TASS -- Russia can join the 
Partnership for Peace programme at the end of March, Russian 
Defence Minister Pavel Grachev told journalists here today after 
his meeting with U.S. Defence Secretary William Perry. 
  "Groups of experts are already completing work on our 
approach to Russia's membership of the Partnership for Peace 
project," the Russian minister said. 
  "Proceeding from Russian specifics, we shall be able to join 
the concept by the end of this month," he explained. 

