<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chief of Armed Forces General Staff Ends Visit to France </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1603185494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1621 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1603185494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Andrey Shtorkh] </F>
  [Text] Paris March 16 TASS -- Russian chief of General 
Staff Colonel-General Mikhail Kolesnikov ended his visit to 
France with a lecture, "Defence Policy and Reorganisation of the 
Russian Armed Forces," at the French military school on 
Wednesday [16 March]. 
  Kolesnikov toured the school located in the French capital 
and had a one-to-one meeting with his French counterpart Jacques 
Lanxade. 
  During his three-day visit, Kolesnikov met with French 
military leaders to discuss French military policy in light of 
the white paper recently issued by the government, France's 
participation in U.N. peace-keeping operations, its relations 
with the Conference on Security and Cooperation in Europe, NATO, 
the Western European Union and Russian-French bilateral 
relations. 
  Kolesnikov also had talks with head of the parliamentary 
defence commission Jacques Bouaillon, visited the air force base 
Mont-de- Marsan where attended air force exercises and an air 
force division in Toulouse. 
  The high-ranking French military believe Kolesnikov's visit 
will help strengthen defence cooperation between Russia and 
France. 

</TEXT>

