<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Invites Saddam Husayn To Attend Party Congress </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1603171494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1555 
GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1603171494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 16 Mar (ITAR-TASS) -- Iraqi President Saddam 
Husayn has been officially invited to attend the congress of the 
Liberal Democratic Party of Russia [LDPR], which opens on 2 
April in Moscow. This has been confirmed by LDPR leader 
Vladimir Zhirinovskiy in response to an inquiry from a 
correspondent for the journal EKHO PLANETY [ECHO OF THE PLANET]. 
"We have invited anybody with whom we maintain relations -- 
people from Iraq, Serbia, North Korea, South Korea, and other 
countries. We have friends everywhere," he said. 
  The sensational news that the president of Taiwan had also 
been invited to the congress and might turn up has not so far 
been confirmed. 
  However, it has been reported from Paris that the first 
deputy leader of the French National Front will definitely come 
to Moscow for the LDPR congress. The head of the extreme 
right-wing German People's Union, Gerhard Frey, also intends to 
take part in it. 

</TEXT>

