<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk, Estonia's Meri Sign Cooperation Accords </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1603132094 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 1207 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1603132094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 16 Mar -- Estonian President Lennart Meri's 
delegation and Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk and 
government officials have held official meetings and 
negotiations. Regarding the results of the negotiations, the 
sides signed agreements on international and cultural 
cooperation. Foreign Minister Anatoliy Zlenko and Culture 
Minister Ivan Dzyuba took part in the signing ceremony. 
  The Estonian president also met the Ukrainian Supreme 
Council 
chairman [Ivan Plyushch]. Ivan Plyushch emphasized the 
timeliness of the Estonian president's visit, as Ukraine is 
currently at the stage of establishing new international 
relations and the world's attitude toward Ukraine is improving. 

</TEXT>

