<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rebels Seize Black Sea Fleet Hospital </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503170794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1402 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1503170794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to sources in the Black Sea Fleet's 
headquarters, Ukrainian servicemen seized the Black Sea Fleet's 
hospital in Ochakov (Ukraine's Nikolayev Region) on 14 March. 
  Ukrainian submachine-gunners do not allow medical personnel 
in, if the latter refuse to take an oath of allegiance to 
Ukraine. 
  Hospital workers said that Major Shevchenko of the Ukrainian 
armed forces had presented them an ultimatum in accordance with 
which they must either serve in the Ukrainian Armed Forces or 
will lose their jobs. 
  A high-ranking representative of the Black Sea Fleet, who 
preferred to remain anonymous, said that earlier this year 
Ukrainian submachine-gunners had seized the military hospital in 
Nikolayev. Special forces were involved. 
  The same source announced that the Black Sea Command 
qualified those actions as "actions carried out by uncontrolled 
bandit formations, because the Ukrainian Defense Ministry did 
not inform the Black Sea Command of its plans to resubordinate 
the Black Sea Fleet's establishments and units." 
  He stated that if such unilateral actions were repeated, the 
Black Sea Fleet personnel would be given the order to use arms 
to rebuff them. 

</TEXT>

