<H3> <TI>   Navy Denies `Seizure' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1603230094 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in English 
2200 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1603230094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] As UKRINFORM's correspondent in Sevastopol, Crimea, 
reported on Wednesday [16 March] the Ukrainian Navy's press 
center refuted a report by the Black Sea Fleet's press center 
about an alleged seizure by the Ukrainian naval personnel of a 
naval hospital in Ochakov. As the Ukrainian statement says, the 
hospital's personnel took an oath of allegiance to Ukraine and 
appealed to the Ukrainian Defense Ministry and Navy command to 
enroll them as the Ukrainian Navy servicemen. Since then, the 
hospital has been strictly guarded, as when a similar situation 
evolved once in Nikolayev. The Black Sea Fleet command 
attempted to take away medical equipment and drugs from the 
local naval hospital, the statement explains. 

</TEXT>

