<H3> <TI>   Press Explains Incident </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1603110194 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 0900 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1603110194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to a report by the Ukrainian Navy press 
center, officers and more than 20 servicemen of the Black Sea 
Fleet's hospital in Ochakiv have asked the Ukrainian Defense 
Ministry and the Ukrainian Navy command to enroll them in the 
Ukrainian Armed Forces. They have recently taken an oath of 
allegiance to the Ukrainian people. The hospital staff 
explained that their decision was based on the fact that they 
are all Ukrainian citizens, and that they were tired of being 
hostages to circumstances, and to feeling the constant 
psychological pressure caused by the uncertainty of their fate. 
To prevent property and equipment from being taken away from 
the hospital, additional security was deployed during the oath. 
The press center report also notes that the command of the 
Black Sea Fleet Ochakiv Division failed to convince the officers 
to change their decision. 

</TEXT>

