<H3> <TI>   Radetskyy Visits Romania, Meets With State Leaders </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1703093294 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 0600 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1703093294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yesterday, a Ukrainian military delegation headed 
by Defense Minister Vitaliy Radetskyy visited Constanta, where 
they met with Vice Admiral George Antonescu, chief of the 
Romanian Navy Joint Chiefs of Staff. They also visited the 
torpedo boat [word indistinct] and the Navy Academy. 
  After returning to Bucharest, Vitaliy Radetskyy met with 
Romanian Foreign Minister Teodor Melescanu. In the course of 
the conversation, the sides emphasized the contribution that 
both countries can make in strengthening security and stability 
in the region that is currently experiencing difficulties. 
  The Ukrainian defense minister was received by Romanian 
President Ion Iliescu. During their talks, a mutual desire to 
develop Romanian-Ukrainian relations in the interests of both 
countries and people was emphasized. 

