<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Blames `Complications' on Meshkov </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1603210394 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 2000 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1603210394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] To begin one's activity in the position of Crimean 
president by violating the Ukrainian Constitution is a challenge 
to democracy. This was said by Ukrainian President Leonid 
Kravchuk at a meeting with Ukrainian and foreign journalists 
today in Kiev. He characterized the actions by Yuriy Meshkov as 
contradictory to the basic law of our state. At the same time, 
Leonid Kravchuk reiterated that during his personal meeting with 
the Crimean president, he proposed to the latter that they hold 
close contacts and take preliminary steps to sort things out in 
Crimea. Meshkov, however, claims that the president of Ukraine 
did not adhere to the agreements, and issued an edict on holding 
a referendum. By the way, even the autonomous Central Election 
Commission expressed hope that he would bring the documents in 
line with Crimean legislation. All responsibility for any 
possible complications will fall upon Mr. Meshkov, stressed 
Leonid Kravchuk. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

