<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Spring-94' Denounces Controlled Media </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1603201694 Minsk BELAPAN in Belarusian 1600 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1603201694 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk BELAPAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Coordinating Council of the </F>
Association of Democratic Forces `Spring-94' Issues a Statement"] 
  [Text] The Coordinating Council of the Association of 
Democratic Forces "Spring-94" has issued a statement denouncing 
the stance of the Belarusian Government regarding the activities 
of the Belarusian mass media. "The prevailing majority of mass 
media are, as before, in the hands of the executive bodies," the 
statement reads. "Leaders of the government overtly declare 
that media which do not support the government will not be 
granted subsidies." The authors of the statement demand that 
space in newspapers and even broadcasting time be issued by the 
government to various parties and political associations to 
allow them the opportunity to clarify their platforms during the 
elections. 

</TEXT>

