<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Full Russian Gas Supplies Resume; Payment Set </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1503204494 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1815 
GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1503204494 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today, Belarus began to receive full gas deliveries 
from Russia. Gasprom resumed supplying its earlier volume of 
blue fuel to the Republic. By the end of Tuesday [15 March], 
deliveries are expected to reach earlier [word indistinct] 
volume of 54 million cubic meters. This was agreed by Russia's 
Gasprom and the Belarusian Beltransgas during their negotiations 
in Moscow. 
  A delegation of gas-industry specialists from Belarus, 
headed 
by Beltransgas Director Mikalay Macharnyak, went to Moscow for 
the sole purpose of discussing conditions for repaying 
Belarusian debts for Russian natural gas deliveries. In line 
with agreements reached with Ukraine's partners, 150 percent [as 
heard] of Belarusian debts for last year's deliveries will be 
settled by financial means while 50 percent will be met by 
supplying Russia's Gasprom with equipment and materiel. This 
year's debt will be settled by financial means. A repayment 
schedule for this quarter has already been agreed upon. An 
agreement in principle has also been reached on the joint 
ownership of property of the territory of Belarus, but the 
actual Russian ownership share will be determined at a later 
date. According to ITAR-TASS, it was determined that a final 
resolution of the questions under discussion will be adopted 
within the next 10 days. 

</TEXT>

