<H3> <TI>   Talks Continue With Russia on Baykonur Site </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1603133894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1144 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1603133894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russia and Kazakhstan are continuing their talks 
concerning the terms of leasing the launching site in Baykonur, 
and signing an agreement on military-technical cooperation. 
  A spokesman for the Russian Space Agency (RSA) told Interfax 
that a delegation led by the Kazakh Prime Minister, Sergey 
Tereshchenko, is arriving in Moscow on Wednesday with this aim 
in view. 
  According to the spokesman, "the delegation includes several 
groups of experts, each specializing in definite area of 
bilateral cooperation." 
  The talks in Moscow pose a third round of bilateral 
endeavors 
to work out documents to be signed by the presidents of the two 
countries in late March. 
  "This time the Kazakh delegation inclines to conclude the 
process of talks, and prepare all the documents for being 
signed, even if it has to stay in Moscow till the end of this 
month." 

</TEXT>

