<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nazarbayev Assigns Kolkhoz Property to Directors </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1603165794 Moscow PRAVDA in Russian 16 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM1603165794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow PRAVDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Tleuzhan Esilbayev: "Directors Will Become </F>
Property Owners by Edict"] 
  [Text] Alma-Ata [Almaty] -- Kazakhstan President Nursultan 
Nazarbayev has signed an edict "On the Transfer of Part of 
Sovkhoz Property to the Ownership of the Directors." On the 
basis of the document in question, a director, having worked for 
20 years in this position, will be allocated 10 percent of the 
redeemable part [vykupnaya chast] of property belonging to a 
state agricultural enterprise on a noncompensatory basis. 
Moreover, he will be given a further 10 percent (the state 
share) of the redeemable part of the property for temporary 
usage for a period of no more than five years. 

</TEXT>

