<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aliyev, World Bank Official Hold Meeting on Aid </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1603210294 Baku Radio Baku International Service in Azeri 
1300 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1603210294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Radio Baku International Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Azeri </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Geydar Aliyev received Mr. Russell 
(Cheetham), director of the World Bank's Europe and Asia 
Department, who is on an official visit to Azerbaijan. The 
guest will hold talks with the republic's leaders and 
representatives of several organizations during his visit. The 
objective of his visit is to familiarize himself with the 
present situation in Azerbaijan and discuss the World Bank's 
draft proposals on aid to the Republic. 
  President Aliyev warmly greeted his guest and informed him 
that he welcomes his visit. Aliyev stressed that he highly 
appreciates the World Bank's effort to cooperate with Azerbaijan 
and the steps it has taken in that direction. 
  Mr. Russell (Cheetham) said that the World Bank plans to 
invest in many economic areas in Azerbaijan. President Aliyev 
informed the guest that the problems he mentioned are vitally 
important. He asserted: Of course, Azerbaijan also has other 
problems. Under the existing conditions, we greatly need the 
World Bank's aid. The World Bank may rest assured that capital 
investments in Azerbaijan will be [word indistinct] for the 
future. 
  Mr. Russell (Cheetham) recalled that the World Bank has 
established relations with the former USSR republics during the 
past two or three years and stressed that it can also share its 
experience with Azerbaijan. 

</TEXT>

