<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Advadze on Abkhazia, Shevardnadze Visit to UN </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1603171294 Yerevan SNARK in English 0916 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1603171294 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, March 16 (SNARK)--"Georgia will never say 
"yes" to the Abkhazia's separation from Georgia. Abkhazians won 
the war, but it's the temporary victory", Valerian Advadze, 
Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary Ambassador of Georgia to 
Russia, told yesterday March 15 at his press-conference in 
Moscow. 
  According to Valerian Advadze, the danger of separatism 
exists not only for Georgia but also for the other countries of 
the world. "The separatism in Abkhazia should be curbed, 
otherwise it will bring to civil wars". 
  So, the Russian Federation should support Georgia otherwise 
Russia will solve the same problems. 
  Mr. Advadze considers the visit of the Georgian leader 
Eduard Shevardnadze to the UN "very successful". The main aim 
of the visit was to convince world community of the necessity to 
introduce the peace-making forces into the zone of the conflict, 
to get the economical aid and political support of the 
Shevardnadze's course. 
  [Yerevan SNARK in English at 0916 in a similarly datelined 
report adds: "Abkhazia is the land of Georgia. It's necessary 
to recognize Abkhazia as a part of the Georgian state to prevent 
the possible bloodshed, Valerian Advadze, Extraordinary and 
Plenipotentiary Ambassador of Georgia to Russia, told in his 
exclusive interview to SNARK. 
  ["According to Mr. Ambassador, Abkhazia is guilty in 
torpedoing peace negotiations as she doesn't recognize the 
territorial integrity of Georgia. 
  ["'World speaks for Georgia and the Shevardnadze's visit to 
the UN confirms such attitude. There doesn't exist any state 
which recognizes the independence of Abkhazia. Abkhazians speak 
against the will of the whole world community', Mr. Advadze 
said."] 

</TEXT>

