<H3> <TI>   Russia's Acceptance of `Partnership' Urged </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1603193494 Tallinn BNS in English 1639 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1603193494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Riga, Mar 16, BNS -- Latvia has to reconcile itself 
with the anticipated participation of Russia in the NATO's 
Partnership for Peace program which is designed for all East 
European countries, MP Indulis Berzins told BNS Wednesday [16 
March]. 
  Latvia will continue its path to the full integration into 
the North Atlantic Treaty Organization because it is the only 
organization capable of extending security guarantees in the 
conditions of foreign jeopardy, Berzins said. 
  NATO extension rests with NATO itself, Berzins noted. 
  Berzins is deputy head of the majority Latvia's Way faction 
and member of the parliament's Foreign Affairs' Committee. 

</TEXT>

