<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 17 Mar (ITAR-TASS) -- Early this morning an 
armed group of persons in military uniform seized the building 
of the town administration in Vladivostok. There is effectively 
no legitimite rule in the town, says a cable from the deputy 
head of administration of the town, received by ITAR-TASS. 
  The Vladivostok mayor's office is blockaded by OMON [Special 
Purpose Militia Detachment] men who have been brought in by 
Lebedinets, vice governor of Maritime Kray. They are not 
allowing lawyer Ulitskiy to see the mayor, although Mayor Viktor 
Cherepkov has been detained, a report from the mayor's office of 
the town points out. The fact that yesterday the mayor had a 
serious heart attack is being ignored, and doctors who arrived 
in an ambulance have told him to stay in bed and have forbidden 
him being questioned. 

