<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Armed Men Enter Vladivostok Mayor's Office </TI></H3>
<H4>   Mayor Faces Criminal Allegations </H4>
<F P=102> LD1703094394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0924 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1703094394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Larisa Beloyvan and Eduard </F>
Popov] 
  [Text] Vladovostok March 17 TASS -- Unrest has been 
sweeping Russia's Far Eastern city of Vladivostok for the second 
consecutive day. On Wednesday, armed riot police stormed the 
mayor's office and told Mayor Viktor Cherepkov and his closest 
aides they were dismissed from office. First Deputy Mayor 
Vladimir Gilgenberg, who put up resistance, was literally 
carried out of the building by police. 
  This was the second armed invasion of the city 
administration 
building. The first occupation occurred on the night from 
February 12-13, and was prompted, according to an official 
version, by the need to question Cherepkov on receiving a bribe 
from a certain Volkov. The mayor then remained at power thanks 
to public support. 
  On Wednesday, the Maritime territorial administration issued 
an order to topple Cherepkov, citing the documents supplied by 
the city prosecutor which say criminal proceedings are being 
established against Cherepkov under Article 170 (Part 3) of the 
Russian Criminal Code (bribe taking). 
  Territorial administration members Konstantin Tolstosheyn 
and 
Vasiliy Terekhov have been named acting mayor and his deputy. 
They had been Cherepkov's rivals in the mayor's elections, but 
flopped, scoring 1.5 percent votes between them. 
  Supporters of the toppled mayor, including a group of voters 
who nominated him to the territorial duma, have announced that 
Cherepkov's toppling was an act of open arbitrariness and a 
gross violation of human rights. They said they would hold acts 
of protest, up to fasting at the territorial administration 
building. 
  The first meeting of protest was held in Vladivostok on 
Thursday night. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

