<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Visits Ship Prior to Christopher Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1703085494 Vladivostok Radiostantsiya Tikhiy Okean 
Maritime Network in Russian 0815 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1703085494 </F>
<F P=104>  Vladivostok Radiostantsiya Tikhiy Okean 
Maritime Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Pacific Ocean" program] </F>
  [Text] Andrey Kozyrev, minister for foreign affairs of the 
Russian Federation, yesterday afternoon visited the Pacific 
Fleet's large antisubmarine ship, Admiral Panteleyev. 
Accompanied by Vice Admiral Igor Khmelnov, first deputy 
commander of the Pacific Fleet, and Yevgeniy Nazdratenko, head 
of the Maritime Kray administration, the guest toured the ship 
and visited the navigation bridge. 
  Subsequently, the minister of foreign affairs went down to 
the ship's wardroom where officers and crew waited for him. In 
a short talk, the minister noted that the Russian Army and the 
fleet, like the country, are experiencing a difficult time. 
However, this is not the first time that this has happened in 
Russia and that is why the Navy must live through it 
appropriately; skillfully defend the fatherland; serve the 
Constitution; and carry out the president's orders. The Pacific 
Fleet is a great fleet and we will strengthen it, and we do not 
intend to divide the other fleets. 
  From the ship, Andrey Kozyrev, minister for foreign affairs, 
set out for Vladivostok Airport where he met Warren Christopher, 
U.S. secretary of state, who had arrived for talks. After the 
talks, a short briefing was held for Russian and foreign 
journalists. 

</TEXT>

