<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Endorses Procedure for Future Hearings </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1603133194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1221 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1603133194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow March 16 TASS -- The State Duma has endorsed 
a procedure for future parliamentary hearings. 
  At its plenary meeting on Wednesday [16 March], the Duma 
directed appropriate committees to arrange for hearings on the 
Partnership-for-Peace documents, which had been adopted at a 
session of the North Atlantic Council in January 1994, on 
matters concerning the implementation of the START I Treaty and 
its realisation problems, an analysis of the status and problems 
of the state border of the Russian Federation, and on the 
Russia's participation in international agreements on the 
elimination of chemical weapons. 
  The Duma will also hold hearings to consider "the results of 
the privatisation of state-run and municipal enterprises of the 
Russian Federation in 1992-1993" and a relevant state programme, 
on structural, science and technology policy, and a concept of 
the Russian Federation's transition to a steady development 
model. 

</TEXT>

