<H3> <TI>   Notes Local Government Election Law Violations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1603164394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1357 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1603164394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow March 16 TASS -- The Russian General 
Prosecutor's Office has received more than 90 reports about 
violations of the Election Law by local bodies of state 
authority in Russian regions, the State Duma was told today. 
Such violations were registered in 23 component parts of the 
federation. The worst was that citizens, servicemen in 
particular, were not allowed to run for seats in local bodies of 
power. 
  The Russian State Duma reaffirmed on Wednesday [16 March] 
its 
intention to pass a bill on guarantees of voters' rights during 
elections to local government. The president as the guarantor 
of the Constitution is recommended to take measures to avert 
such violations. 

</TEXT>

