<F P=102>  LD1603132194 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1000 GMT 
16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1603132194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Virgilijus Bulovas, the head of Lithuania's working 
group at the talks with CIS countries, has confirmed to Interfax 
that the next round of talks between Russia and Lithuania will 
take place in Moscow on 21-22 March. Despite the fact that the 
previous meeting of the delegations was held in September 1993, 
Bulovas said that the Russian-Lithuanian negotiations were going 
well. The sides agreed that the main volume of work was to be 
done at a level of groups of experts. Bulovas said that the 
list of issues that were to be discussed at the new round of 
talks was not yet finalized. However, he believes that the 
discussion is likely to focus on border crossing and travel from 
one state to another. These problems were discussed at last 
week's meeting of groups of experts. 

