<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Issues Instruction on Work of Appeals Commission </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1703112494 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 
17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1703112494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Yeltsin has issued an instruction on 
certain questions regarding the work of the commission for 
questions of appeals under the president of the Russian 
Federation. In accordance with the document, as the president's 
press service has reported, the commission is due to examine 
applications for appeals by persons condemned to capital 
punishment and to prepare a draft decree of the president on the 
pardoning of such persons. The criminal code says that in the 
event of the commutation of capital punishment on appeal to 
deprivation of freedom, it may be fixed for a period of up to 15 
years or for life. 

</TEXT>

