<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iranian Plane Crashes in Nagorno-Karabakh </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803104094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1028 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1803104094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow March 18 TASS -- 32 people were killed when 
an Iranian C-130 transport plane crashed three kilometres north 
of Stepanakert, the capital of Nagorno-Karabakh, overnight. 
  The plane took off from the Moscow International 
Sheremetyevo-2 Airport at 18.46 Moscow time /15.46 GMT/ bound 
for Tehran. 
  There were 19 family members of the employees of the Iranian 
Embassy in Moscow and 13 crew members, TASS learned on Friday 
from the Ministry for Emergency Situations. 
  The causes of the crash are being investigated. 

</TEXT>

