<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   No Agreement on Outlawing Blockades </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803103794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0947 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1803103794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Yermakova] </F>
  [Text] St. Petersburg March 18 TASS -- The Council of the 
CIS Interparliamentary Assembly, meeting in St. Petersburg on 
Friday [18 March], could not reach a decision on the proposal, 
"on the unacceptability of implementing a blockade against 
member-countries of the Commonwealth of Independent States." As 
a result, the assembly's plenary session opened one hour later 
than scheduled. 
  Chairman of the assembly's council Vladimir Shumeyko 
reported 
that the delegations "could not achieve a consensus concerning 
one of the items in the agenda," noting that he "would not want 
to spread any information about the reasons for the 
disagreement." 
  The representatives of the delegations from Armenia and 
Azerbaijan had entirely opposite opinions concerning the 
proposal. Therefore, the participants of the plenary meeting 
decided to ask the delegation heads to converse with their 
colleagues during the break and decide if it is worthwhile to 
leave the blockade issue in the agenda for the assembly's 
current session. 
  Shumeyko expressed his opinion that everybody understands 
how 
difficult it is to resolve such questions. He said the assembly 
members had agreed to continue work on the blockade proposal and 
introduce it during the assembly's next meeting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

