<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Assembly Chairman on Social Charter </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803112394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1023 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1803112394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Svetlana Ivanova] </F>
  [Text] St. Petersburg March 18 TASS -- Commonwealth 
Interparliamentary Assembly Chairman Vladimir Shumeyko called on 
member countries to work out the Commonwealth's social charter 
to provide protection and guarantees to Commonwealth citizens in 
the social and labor sphere and supervise the fulfillment of 
interstate accords. 
  He said a social charter is needed to supplement the 
agreement on the economic alliance designed to offset the burden 
of ruptured economic links inside the former Soviet Union which 
was "built like one huge factory." 
  Shumeyko, who urged the search for new forms of cooperation 
within the Commonwealth in the cultural, economic, political and 
military fields, said a new legal infrastructure was needed to 
remove barriers from the path of economic and financial 
cooperation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

