<H3> <TI>   Republic Defense Ministry Sets Up TV, Radio Studio </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1803092394 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 17 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM1803092394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Valeriy Kovalev under "In Brief" rubric: </F>
"Belorusian `Slavyanka' Goes on Air"] 
  [Text] Minsk -- A television and radio broadcasting studio 
has been set up under the Ministry of Defense of Belorusia 
[Belarus]. It is staffed by 28 creative and technical workers 
who will prepare television and radio broadcasts on military 
subjects. The Defense Ministry hopes that the military 
television and radio studio will make it possible to provide 
more prompt and, most importantly, more objective coverage of 
the life, combat training, and service of servicemen and will 
help to enhance their authority in the eyes of their fellow 
citizens. Topics prepared by military television journalists 
are already used in national television news programs. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

