<F P=103> LD1703182794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The press service of the president of Crimea issued 
a statement today in connection with the 12 March 1994 
resolution by the Central Electoral Commission on the elections 
to the Supreme Council of the Crimea Republic. The statement 
indicates that in his decree "On Conducting a Poll Among the 
Citizens of the Crimea Republic on 27 March," President Yuriy 
Meshkov was guided by the electors' will and also took into 
account the refusal of the Supreme Council of Crimea to lift a 
moratorium on holding an all-Crimean referendum. 
  In setting the date of the poll, the president was guided by 
the fact that with the assistance of the Central Electoral 
Commission, significant organizational and material losses could 
be avoided in the course of conducting the poll and electing 
deputies to the Supreme Council of Crimea. The document 
underlines that the president will continue taking into account 
the Crimea citizens' will while solving the most important state 
issues. 

