<H3> <TI>   Fire Reported at Khmelnytskyy Nuclear Power Plant </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1703140394 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 1100 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1703140394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] As the Ukrainian Interior Ministry General Fire 
Department has reported, on 16 March at 2045 [local time], a 
fire erupted in the engine room at the first power unit of the 
Khmelnytskyy nuclear power plant in a cable box housing power 
and control cables. 
  The chiefs of the plant's fire department decided to deploy 
firefighters in the danger zone to extinguish the 6,000-volt 
cables. The firefighters wore special gear. In addition, to the 
firefighters' action, the plant personnel stopped the operation 
of the first power unit reactor. [passage indistinct] 
  The fire was extinguished at 2110. The damages are currently 
being assessed. According to preliminary assessments, the fire 
was caused by a short circuit in the main power cable. The 
radiation level remains normal. 

</TEXT>

