<F P=102>  LD1703221494 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
2020 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1703221494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By O. Sayfulin; from the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The prime ministers of Russia and Kazakhstan held a 
working meeting today. They discussed issues concerning 
bilateral economic cooperation, dual citizenship, and the use of 
the Baykonur cosmodrome. 
  It has become known that there will be no obstacles for the 
citizens of Kazakhstan to receive temporary citizenship in 
Russia and to change it when they return to Kazakhstan. 
  As for Baykonur, it can be handed over to Russia after 
signing a lease treaty. The price remains the only point issue. 
In addition, the prime minister of Kazakhstan said it that was 
also necessary to resolve ecological problems when using the 
cosmodrome. Ecological compensation should be defined. As of 
today, the financing of Baykonur remains the main issue. As for 
its technical safety, one should not worry about this. 
Accommodation for families of Russian officers and servicing 
personnel on Kazakhstan territory will also not pose a problem. 
  [Begin Tereshchenko recording] The programs that are to be 
implemented on Baykonur demand large investments. Presently, 
there are not enough of them either from Russia or Kazakhstan. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

