<H3> <TI>   Nation Unlikely To Join Partnership for Peace Program </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1603194394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1638 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1603194394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kyrgyzstan will most likely not join NATO's 
Partnership for Peace program, said an aide to the Kyrgyz 
president. 
  Bakyt Abdrisayev told INTERFAX on Wednesday that Kyrgyzstan 
was giving the matter careful consideration, since the Central 
Asian republic had commitments under CIS collective security 
agreements. 
  Kyrgyz Defense Ministry spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Akzhal 
Isayev told Interfax the same day that the ministry was still 
unfamiliar with NATO's program and therefore had no position on 
it. 

