<DOCNO> FBIS3-16592 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov053_o_94002" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-053 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  17 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Uzbekistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bank Refutes Early Introduction of National Currency </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1703114694 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 0900 GMT 
17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1703114694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Central Bank of Uzbekistan has refuted reports 
that the Republic was going to introduce a permanent national 
currency in April to replace the temporary sum coupon. The bank 
said that this would happen in the second half of the year. 
Meanwhile, the fall of the sum coupon is continuing. Its 
market exchange rate against the ruble is nine to one. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

