<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Delegation To Attend CIS Interparliamentary Council </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1703221494 Baku Radio Baku Network in Azeri 1700 GMT 17 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1703221494 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Radio Baku Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Azeri </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Afiyeddin Dzhelilov, deputy chairman of the 
Azerbaijan Supreme Soviet, has said that the CIS 
Interparliamentary Council meeting in Saint Petersburg will 
discuss the dispute between Armenia and Azerbaijan, in addition 
to other issues. Afiyeddin Dzhelilov is heading a delegation to 
Saint Petersburg. He disclosed at a briefing he held before he 
left Baku that the Interparliamentary Council will discuss the 
dispute between the two republics. 
  Dzhelilov recalled that the Interparliamentary Council's 
previous session was briefed by the republic's delegation on the 
dispute and Azerbaijan's approach; and he stressed that the 
republic's representatives will reiterate Azerbaijan's position 
on the peaceful settlement of the dispute when the Council meets 
on 18 March. Azerbaijan's position has already been explained by 
the republic's leaders several times. 
  The journalists were informed that the Interparliamentary 
Council's permanent committees deliberated on economic and 
financial issues, protection of the environment, social 
policies, and other matters a few days ago. They also set the 
agenda of the Council. Dzhelilov said that several 
representatives from the Azerbaijan National Assembly attended 
the permanent committee meetings. He also said that the 
republic's delegation has made plans to hold talks with the 
parliamentary representatives of the Russian Federation, 
Belarus, and Georgia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

