<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament Session Postponed; PFA Complains </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1703193494 Baku TURAN in English 1656 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1703193494 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku, March 17 (TURAN) -- The session of Milli 
Majlis which [was] scheduled for March 17, at 12.00 a.m. has 
been postponed, reports national TV. 
  The agenda included discussion of the results of the 
Armenian-Azerbaijani talks on March 12, and the intent by the 
Popular Front to carry out a coup d'etat on March 5. 
  Yesterday, the deputies of the PFA [People's Front of 
Azerbaijan] and the leader of the National Independence Party, 
Etibar Mamedov, said that they will raise the issue of the 
harassment and persecution of the independent press and the 
concluding truce with Armenia which is disadvantageous for 
Azerbaijan. 

</TEXT>

