<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Amnesty for Political Crimes Restricted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1703215894 Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network in Azeri 1600 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1703215894 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Azeri </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Law on restrictions on the implementation of amnesty acts; </F>
date of issue not given -- read by announcer] 
  [Text] With the aim of strengthening the struggle against 
the criminal acts committed against the Azerbaijani Republic's 
sovereignty and territorial integrity, to ensure real 
accountability of people involved in such crimes, and to improve 
the country's defensive capability, the Azerbaijani National 
Assembly decides that: 
  The application of the amnesty acts is hereby banned in the 
case of people involved in crimes connected with the illegal 
introduction of the Soviet troops into Baku on 19-20 January 
1990, the massacre in Khodzhaly, and the occupation of the 
Azerbaijani Republic's territory by the Armenian Armed Forces. 
  [signed] Geydar Aliyev, president of Azerbaijan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
